# Project Rules: Flutter Mobile App

> Cross-platform mobile application built with Flutter and Dart.

## Project Identity

- **Type**: Mobile App (iOS + Android)
- **Language**: Dart 3.0+
- **Framework**: Flutter 3.x
- **State**: Riverpod 2.0
- **Navigation**: GoRouter
- **Testing**: flutter_test + integration_test

---

## Coding Standards

### Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Files | snake_case | `user_profile_screen.dart` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `UserProfileScreen` |
| Variables | camelCase | `userName` |
| Constants | camelCase with `k` prefix | `kDefaultPadding` |
| Providers | camelCase with `Provider` suffix | `userProvider` |

### File Organization

```
lib/
├── main.dart
├── app/
│   ├── app.dart           # MaterialApp configuration
│   └── router.dart        # GoRouter setup
├── features/
│   └── auth/
│       ├── data/           # Repository, data sources
│       ├── domain/         # Entities, use cases
│       └── presentation/   # Screens, widgets, providers
├── shared/
│   ├── widgets/            # Reusable widgets
│   ├── theme/              # ThemeData, colors, typography
│   └── utils/              # Helpers
└── l10n/                   # Localization
```

---

## Critical Rules (🔴)

### Rule 1: ❌ Never use setState for complex state

```dart
// ❌ BAD — setState for anything beyond simple local UI
class _MyWidgetState extends State<MyWidget> {
  List<User> users = [];
  void _loadUsers() async {
    users = await api.getUsers();
    setState(() {});
  }
}

// ✅ GOOD — Riverpod for state management
final usersProvider = FutureProvider<List<User>>((ref) async {
  return ref.read(userRepositoryProvider).getUsers();
});
```

### Rule 2: ✅ Always use const constructors

```dart
// ❌ BAD
return Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.all(16));

// ✅ GOOD
return const Padding(padding: EdgeInsets.all(16));
```

---

## Code Smells to Avoid

| ❌ Smell | ✅ Instead Do |
|----------|--------------|
| Widget tree > 100 lines | Extract into smaller widgets |
| Hardcoded strings | Use `l10n` for all user-facing text |
| Hardcoded colors | Use `Theme.of(context)` |
| `Navigator.push()` | Use GoRouter for type-safe navigation |
